nd I loved the way he played", "doc_title": "Ellen Rowe interviewed by Monk Rowe, via Zoom, December 2, 2024", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/ellen-rowe-interviewed-monk-rowe-zoom-december-2-2024"}, {"speaker": "Josiah Gluck", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "Or some early Elton John or Jethro Tull, things like that. I’d just love to hear how that all sounds", "doc_title": "Josiah Gluck interviewed by Monk Rowe, via Zoom, July 13, 2022", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/josiah-gluck-interviewed-monk-rowe-zoom-july-13-2022"}, {"speaker": "Paul Shaffer", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "I was just such a big Elton fan, still am... that's how much I liked him.", "doc_title": "Paul Shaffer interviewed by Monk Rowe, via Zoom, August 24, 2023", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/paul-shaffer-interviewed-monk-rowe-zoom-august-24-2023"}, {"speaker": "Lew Soloff", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "Elton John, Billy Joel, Sting... Stevie Wonder sat in. And I’ll tell you it was just thrilling. It was thrilling to play this music with these people.", "doc_title": "Lew Soloff interviewed by Monk Rowe, Scottsdale, Arizona, April 16, 2000", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/lew-soloff-interviewed-monk-rowe-scottsdale-arizona-april-16-2000"}, {"speaker": "Jon Hendricks", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "When I lived in London, the Monday night relief player at Ronnie Scott’s was Elton John. He was trying to sound like Horace Silver.", "doc_title": "Jon Hendricks — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://americanhistory.si.edu/sites/default/files/file-uploader/Jon-Hendricks-Transcription-2020.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Keith Ingham", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "I mean the music of today I think is Elton John and the things that relate to people now", "doc_title": "Keith Ingham interviewed by Monk Rowe, Chautauqua, New York, September 12, 1997", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/keith-ingham-interviewed-monk-rowe-chautauqua-new-york-september-12-1997"}]}